#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/coco.md:1
msgid "Using Asterinas as a Confidential Containers Guest Kernel"
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/coco.md:3
msgid ""
"This guide explains how to use Asterinas as the guest kernel for "
"Confidential Containers (CoCo)."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/coco.md:6
msgid ""
"[Confidential Containers](https://github.com/confidential-containers/"
"confidential-containers) is a VM-based containers stack built on [Kata "
"Containers](https://github.com/kata-containers/kata-containers) and "
"protected with [confidential computing](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Confidential_computing) technology. It runs pods inside confidential virtual "
"machines (CVMs) while integrating with Kubernetes and confidential computing "
"workflows. If you only need VM-based isolation without confidential "
"computing, see [Using Asterinas as a Kata Guest Kernel](kata.md) instead."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/coco.md:14
msgid ""
"This guide uses the [Asterinas fork of Confidential Containers](https://"
"github.com/asterinas/confidential-containers), which carries Asterinas-"
"specific patches, helper scripts, and configuration for building, "
"installing, and testing CoCo with Asterinas as the guest kernel."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/coco.md:20
msgid "The current Asterinas-based CoCo setup supports two paths:"
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/coco.md:22
msgid "a regular CoCo runtime for local development and debugging"
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/coco.md:23
msgid "a [Intel TDX](../intel-tdx.md)\\-powered CoCo runtime for CVMs"
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/coco.md:25
msgid "Step 1: Prepare the host kernel"
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/coco.md:27
msgid ""
"CoCo requires a host with KVM and vhost support. The commands in this guide "
"are currently written for x86-64 hosts."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/coco.md:30
msgid "Verify that the required device nodes exist:"
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/coco.md:36
msgid "If any of them are missing, load the matching kernel modules:"
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/coco.md:41
msgid "# Or use kvm_amd on AMD hosts.\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/coco.md:45
msgid ""
"Then make sure the user running Docker can access `/dev/kvm` and `/dev/vhost-"
"vsock`."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/coco.md:48
msgid ""
"If you plan to use the TDX-powered CoCo runtime, your host additionally "
"requires Intel TDX hardware support, a TDX-capable host kernel, and the TDX "
"firmware modules. See [Intel TDX](../intel-tdx.md) for the full list of TDX "
"prerequisites."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/coco.md:53
msgid "Step 2: Enter the CoCo environment"
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/coco.md:55
msgid ""
"We provide the `asterinas/coco` image with CoCo and Asterinas preinstalled. "
"End users should use it directly. Kernel developers should additionally "
"mount the local Asterinas source."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/coco.md:59
msgid "Step 2.1: Prepare Docker arguments"
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/coco.md:61
msgid "Define the following Docker arguments:"
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/coco.md:73
msgid "These flags are required for CoCo:"
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/coco.md:75
msgid ""
"`--cgroupns host` shares the host cgroup namespace so that `containerd` "
"inside the container can manage CoCo workloads."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/coco.md:77
msgid "`--privileged` is required for KVM and nested container management."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/coco.md:78
msgid ""
"`--device /dev/kvm` and `--device /dev/vhost-vsock` expose the "
"virtualization devices that CoCo needs."
msgstr ""

#: src/kernel/vm-based-containers/coco.md:81
msgid ""
"`--tmpfs /var/lib/containerd-nydus:rw,size=512m` gives the nydus image "
"service enough temporary storage space for guest-side image pulling."
msgstr ""

